<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">COCONUT CHICKEN CURRY</div>

<div class="article-byline" id="ByLine">BY ELIZABETH NELSON</div>

<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page022.article002.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY WILLIAM DICKEY</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 6 to 8 servings</p><br/><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons butter </p><p class="no-indent">3 pounds boneless skinless chicken breast, cut into bite-size pieces </p><p class="no-indent">2 carrots, peeled and sliced ¼-inch thick </p><p class="no-indent">1 tablespoon minced fresh ginger </p><p class="no-indent">2 cloves garlic, minced </p><p class="no-indent">1 tablespoon red curry powder </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup chicken broth </p><p class="no-indent">1 (13.66-ounce) can coconut milk* </p><p class="no-indent">2 pounds yellow potatoes, peeled and cut into bite-size pieces</p><p class="no-indent">1 cup sour cream </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons fresh lime juice </p><p class="no-indent">Garnish: fresh chopped cilantro</p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 325°. Melt butter in a Dutch oven over medium heat. Working in batches, add chicken, and cook for 5 minutes or until browned on all sides. Once all chicken is browned, remove from pan and set aside. Add carrots, ginger, and garlic to pan. Cook for 3 minutes. Stir in curry powder, and cook for 2 minutes. Stir in chicken broth, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer until reduced by half. Stir in chicken, coconut milk, and potatoes. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. Cover and bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken and potatoes are tender. Remove from oven, and cool for 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and lime juice. Garnish with cilantro, if desired. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">*Do not substitute low-fat coconut milk.</p></div>
